{#-
  Cover-letter base template (T12.14).

  Output: Markdown. The downstream pipeline (T12.15/T12.16) feeds this
  through the ``markdown`` library and then WeasyPrint to produce PDF.

  Safety contract
  ---------------
  * Render with Jinja2 ``autoescape=True``. All worker-supplied
    fields (``opening``, ``body``, ``fair_chance_framing``, ``name``,
    ``hiring_manager``) are escaped.
  * No ``| safe`` escape hatches in this template. If a caller needs
    rich markdown in the body they must run ``apply_worker_voice``
    and accept that HTML-ish fragments will be rendered as literal
    text.
-#}
{{ date_today }}

Dear {{ hiring_manager or "Hiring Manager" }},

{{ opening }}

{{ body }}

{% if fair_chance_framing -%}
{{ fair_chance_framing }}
{%- endif %}

Thank you for your consideration.

Sincerely,
{{ name }}
